Package: metamanager
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, jq, inotify-tools, libimage-exiftool-perl, libjpeg-turbo-progs, optipng, webp, ffmpeg
Recommends: wp-cli
Description: Lossless image compression and metadata embedding for WordPress
 Metamanager provides lossless image compression (jpegtran, optipng, cwebp),
 bidirectional EXIF/IPTC/XMP metadata sync via ExifTool, and video/audio
 metadata handling via ffmpeg — all driven by OS-level daemons so WordPress
 or wp-cron are not on the hot path.
 .
 This package ships the WordPress plugin, the compress and metadata daemons,
 and their systemd units. The postinst runs metamanager-install.sh --no-deps,
 which auto-detects the WordPress content directory (probing /srv/www/wordpress,
 /var/www/html, and others), copies the plugin into place, patches the daemon
 scripts and systemd units with the detected path, enables and starts both
 daemons, and activates the plugin via WP-CLI if available.
